object.script:
function onTick() gpsx = input.getNumber(1) gpsy = input.getNumber(2) velocity = input.getNumber(3) depth = 0 - input.getNumber(4) heading = (input.getNumber(8) * -360) % 360 touch = input.getBool(1) output.setNumber(4, input.getNumber(4)) output.setNumber(5, input.getNumber(5)) output.setNumber(6, input.getNumber(6)) output.setNumber(7, input.getNumber(7)) output.setNumber(8, input.getNumber(8)) output.setBool(32, radar_mode) end
function onDraw()
local w, h w = screen.getWidth()*.66 h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(0, 0, 0) screen.drawClear() screen.setColor(0, 255, 0)
local text text = string.format("SPD:%.2f
HDG:%.0f
GPS:
%.0f,%.0f
DEP:%.0f", velocity, heading, gpsx, gpsy, depth) screen.drawTextBox(8, 0, w, h, text) end

function init_contacts(n)
local result={} local i for i=1,n,1 do result[i]={null,null,null} end return result end
function intcomp(x,y) return math.abs(x-y)<0.5 end
-- Divide the sweep into n arcs, each of which are checked for a sonar return slices=16 slice=1 contacts=init_contacts(slices) azimuth=0
-- fov of each slice arc in turns slice_fov=1/slices
function gn(n) input.getNumber(n) end function pn(n, v) output.setNumber(n, v) end
function slice_azimuth(i) local az=(i-1)*slice_fov return az end
-- normalize an angle in turns so that it falls in the range [-.5,.5] -- because otherwise the game will get confused function normturns(t) t=t%1 if(t>0.5) then t=t-1 end return t end
function onTick() detect=input.getBool(1) if(detect) then range=input.getNumber(5) else range=null end elevation=input.getNumber(6) strength=input.getNumber(7) contacts[slice][1]=range contacts[slice][2]=elevation contacts[slice][3]=strength
if(intcomp(slice,slices)) then slice=0 end slice=slice+1
azimuth=slice_azimuth(slice)
-- Sonar seems to orient clockwise no mater how the indicator arrows are oriented -- Since it's mounted upside-down, we have to reverse the azimuth -- The offset backwards is found to be necessary in testing and increases as the FOV decreases pn(7,normturns(0-azimuth+slice_fov*5)) pn(8,slice_fov) end
function ray(turns,r) local x=cx+math.sin(turns*math.pi*2)*r local y=cy-math.cos(turns*math.pi*2)*r return {x,y} end
function contact(i,r,str) local theta=slice_azimuth(i) local theta1=theta+slice_fov/2 local theta2=theta-slice_fov/2 local ray1=ray(theta1,r) local ray2=ray(theta2,r) screen.drawTriangleF(cx,cy,ray1[1],ray1[2],ray2[1],ray2[2])
-- DEBUG -- screen.setColor(255,0,0) -- screen.drawText(0,0,string.format("%i\n%.02f",i,slice_azimuth(i))) end
function onDraw()
local w=screen.getWidth() / 3 local h=screen.getHeight() local r=math.min(w,h)/2-1 cx=screen.getWidth()*5/6 cy=h/2
screen.setColor(0,16,0) screen.drawCircle(cx,cy,r) screen.setColor(0,255,0)
local i for i=1,slices,1 do if(contacts[i][1] ~=null ) then contact(i,r,contacts[i][3]) end end
-- Overdraw the range to the 12o'clock contact whenever present -- Sonar seems to be bugged and returns 0 range and signal strengths, -- so this will remain commented out --[[ if(contacts[1][1]~=null ) then screen.setColor(255,0,0) screen.drawText(0,0,string.format("%.2fm",contacts[1][3])) end ]] end

object.script:
-- Not accurate until the buffer fills, but who cares, takes a moment to spin up an engine anyway
bsize=10 function bufinit() local tmp={} local i for i=1,bsize do tmp[i]=0 end return tmp end
buffer=bufinit() bufpos=0 accum=0
function sum(set,sz) local i local a=0 for i=1,sz do a=a+set[i] end return a end
function onTick() v=input.getNumber(1) bufpos=bufpos+1
if bufpos > bsize+.5 then bufpos=1 buffer[1]=v accum=sum(buffer,bsize) else accum=accum-buffer[bufpos]+v buffer[bufpos]=v end output.setNumber(1,accum/bsize) end
function onDraw() end
